## Commands agents should know (non-exhaustive)

- **Tests (Nexus contracts):** `npm test`
- **Prod HTML vs local git:** `npm run verify:prod-build`
- **Dashboard route shell:** `npm run guard:dashboard-route-shell`
- **Nexus tools live:** `npm run verify:nexus-tools-live` (needs env / JWT per MEMORY)
- **Edge deploy:** `npm run deploy:edge:make-server`
- **Vercel prod CLI:** `npm run deploy:vercel:prod` (requires CLI auth)

## Protected surfaces

Do **not** edit files listed in **`.cursor/rules/02-protected-files-never-touch.mdc`** unless the user explicitly overrides.

## Ingestion reality (Cursor)

- **Project Rules** (this folder) = what the agent always sees in compressed form.
- **Full MEMORY.md** = read on demand per bootstrap rule **`00-session-bootstrap.mdc`**; there is no separate “embed MEMORY into Cursor vector DB” in this repo—**keeping MEMORY.md curated + linking here is the intended pattern.**

When the user says “remember SyncScript production,” **update `MEMORY.md`** (and **`SESSION_START.md`** if workflow changes)—not only chat history.
